abstract: Former Arizona state Treasurer Jeff DeWit is stepping down as chief financial officer at NASA, leaving a job he accepted nearly two years ago after helping run President Donald Trump’s 2016 election campaign.
snippet: Former Arizona state Treasurer Jeff DeWit is stepping down as chief financial officer at NASA, leaving a job he accepted nearly two years ago after helping run President Donald Trump’s 2016 election campaign.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — Former Arizona state Treasurer Jeff DeWit is stepping down as chief financial officer at NASA, leaving a job he accepted nearly two years ago after helping run President Donald Trump’s 2016 election campaign.
headline_main: Ex-Arizona Treasurer to Step Down as NASA CFO to Return Home
headline_print_headline: Ex-Arizona Treasurer to Step Down as NASA CFO to Return Home

abstract: Lawmakers who flipped Republican districts in 2018 worry that a democratic socialist at the top of the ticket could doom their re-election chances.
snippet: Lawmakers who flipped Republican districts in 2018 worry that a democratic socialist at the top of the ticket could doom their re-election chances.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As Bernie Sanders emerges as the leader in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination, his rise is generating fears among centrist Democrats that the apparent leftward shift of their party could cost them not only a chance to retake the White House, but also their hold on the majority in the House of Representatives and their shot at winning the Senate.

abstract: NATO defense ministers agreed on Wednesday to expand the Western alliance's training mission in Iraq, NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg said, responding to a demand by U.S. President Donald Trump for NATO to do more in the Middle East.
snippet: NATO defense ministers agreed on Wednesday to expand the Western alliance's training mission in Iraq, NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg said, responding to a demand by U.S. President Donald Trump for NATO to do more in the Middle East.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — NATO defense ministers agreed on Wednesday to expand the Western alliance's training mission in Iraq, NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg said, responding to a demand by U.S. President Donald Trump for NATO to do more in the Middle East.
headline_main: NATO to Expand Iraq Training Mission in Response to Trump
headline_print_headline: NATO to Expand Iraq Training Mission in Response to Trump

abstract: Ms. Shelton, President Trump’s nominee to the central bank, has unconventional views. But a recent policy reversal is stoking the most concern.
snippet: Ms. Shelton, President Trump’s nominee to the central bank, has unconventional views. But a recent policy reversal is stoking the most concern.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senators will vet Judy Shelton, a prominent Federal Reserve critic, for one of the central bank’s top jobs on Thursday, a moment that many economists will be watching closely because they see her as a potential threat to the Fed’s prized independence.

abstract: Former Massachusetts Governor Deval Patrick withdrew from the race for the 2020 Democratic U.S. presidential nomination on Wednesday, failing to win enough support after a late entry into the crowded field.
snippet: Former Massachusetts Governor Deval Patrick withdrew from the race for the 2020 Democratic U.S. presidential nomination on Wednesday, failing to win enough support after a late entry into the crowded field.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Massachusetts Governor Deval Patrick withdrew from the race for the 2020 Democratic U.S. presidential nomination on Wednesday, failing to win enough support after a late entry into the crowded field.
headline_main: Former Governor Deval Patrick Withdraws From Democratic Presidential Race
headline_print_headline: Former Governor Deval Patrick Withdraws From Democratic Presidential Race

abstract: Mexico's foreign minister said on Wednesday the number of migrants returned to Mexico to await the outcome of U.S. immigration cases has fallen significantly, although activists said large numbers of people remain in the program.
snippet: Mexico's foreign minister said on Wednesday the number of migrants returned to Mexico to await the outcome of U.S. immigration cases has fallen significantly, although activists said large numbers of people remain in the program.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexico's foreign minister said on Wednesday the number of migrants returned to Mexico to await the outcome of U.S. immigration cases has fallen significantly, although activists said large numbers of people remain in the program.
headline_main: Mexico Says U.S. Returning Sharply Fewer Migrants Under 'Remain in Mexico'
headline_print_headline: Mexico Says U.S. Returning Sharply Fewer Migrants Under 'Remain in Mexico'

abstract: The former Massachusetts governor had a compelling life story and an extensive résumé, but his 11th-hour entry into the Democratic primary hurt him.
snippet: The former Massachusetts governor had a compelling life story and an extensive résumé, but his 11th-hour entry into the Democratic primary hurt him.
lead_paragraph: Former Gov. Deval Patrick of Massachusetts dropped out of the Democratic presidential race on Wednesday, just three months after entering it, ending a last-minute campaign that seemed to fizzle out almost as soon as it had begun.

abstract: An undercover video recorded by animal welfare activists shows vendors at a recent trophy-hunting convention promoting trips to shoot captive-bred lions in Africa, despite past public assurances by the event's organizers that so-called canned hunts wouldn't be sold.
